  "text": "Psychiatric symptoms in hyperthyroidism, such as anxiety or mania, appear to be mediated by beta-adrenergic hyperactivity. Accordingly, psychiatric symptoms and psychiatric disorders secondary to hyperthyroidism should be first treated by restoring the euthyroid state. Additional treatment with beta-adrenergic antagonists is also helpful. Antimanic agents are required only when symptoms fail to respond to these measures [CITATION_1] .",
